cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with logic programming and introduces a new type of goal formula in computability logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses default reasoning, which is a common topic in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes a high-level way to express priority-related operations in logic programming. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses exception handling, which is an important aspect of software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new type of goal formula that can be seen as a data structure for specifying tasks with failure-handling routines.
